commit.message:
Fix highlighting identifier containing underscores and keywords

Fixes https://github.com/swift-emacs/swift-mode/issues/190

Open .swiftinterface files in Swift mode

These files were being opened in the default Fundamental mode.

Add value and type parameter packs

https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0393-parameter-packs.md
https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0398-variadic-types.md
https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0399-tuple-of-value-pack-expansion.md

Unfortunately, `repeat` can also be used as `repeat {...} while`, and it
is not properly indented at this time.

Update for Emacs 29

- Update CI
- Update indentations

Fix current-defun-name to support qualified name

Example: `extension A<T>.B.C<U>`.

Add keywords for conditional compilation and annotations

- `hasFeature`
  https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0362-piecemeal-future-features.md
- `hasAttribute`
  https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0367-conditional-attributes.md
- `before`
  https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0376-function-back-deployment.md
- Various environments
Fix command line option for debugging swift module

Fix repl-executable for Swift 5.7

Swift 5.5: `repl` is not mentioned in the manual but is ignored silently.
Swift 5.6: `repl` is the default subcommand.
Swift 5.7: `repl` is not default.
If byte compilation fails, exit test immediately
Update GitHub Action action/checkout to v3

Exclude regex ending with spaces or tabs

https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/commit/d9cae77aef0142944daf953b4bd227edc7fb239c#diff-1f63d0b96db9d2236f665756eae4dcbe5ad40270963a936cb14522ffbc4136ecR222

Improve performance of beginning/end-of-defun

Improve performance of `which-function':
https://github.com/swift-emacs/swift-mode/issues/180

Add comments about workaround

Those workarounds are no longer necessary since 29.1.
